                      <div class="slide-info">
                        <span class="counter">4 of 11</span>
                        <span class="credit">Getty Images</span>
                      </div>
                    
                      <div class="media-body clearfix">
                        <h2>
                            Stretch it out
                        </h2>  
                          <div class="caption margin-24-bottom">Assuming you are pain-free, Reininger says you should try to stretch all of your joints each day to the extent that it does not cause you pain. <br /><br />A physical therapist or other physician can help tailor a stretching program for your needs. <br /><br />People with RA tend to feel stiffer in the morning than at other times of the day, so take a shower to warm up your joints, and then stretch  to help loosen you up for the rest of the day, Reininger advises.</div>
                    
                      </div>
                    </div>
