                      <div class="media-body clearfix">
                        <h2>
                            Take a warm bath or shower
                        </h2>  
                          <div class="caption margin-24-bottom">Moist heat in particular seems to penetrate well and provides relief from rheumatoid arthritis pain, according to Reininger. <br /><br />She recommends taking a warm bath or shower or soaking sore hands in warm water. <br /><br /> Additionally, moist heating pads, available at most pharmacies, can be applied for 10 to 15 minutes at a time to provide temporary pain relief.</div>
                    
