                      <div class="media-body clearfix">
                        <h2>
                            Try hot wax
                        </h2>  
                          <div class="caption margin-24-bottom">If you have pain in the joints of the hands or feet, a hot wax bath can ease inflammation. (This is a classic technique used for sports-related injuries.)<br /><br />Reininger says this can work better than a heating pad because, as with soaking in a warm water bath, the heat works its way completely around the fingers or toes. <br /><br />These hot wax baths, which Reininger says that some patients prefer, can be found online or at drug stores.</div>
                    
                      </div>
